# __TASK_NAME__ Codex Exec Eval

This folder is a self-contained `codex exec` evaluation and skill-improvement harness.

## What to edit first

1. Open `codex-eval.json` and confirm the model, sandbox, target skill path, and optimization settings.
2. Edit `prompts/task-prompt.md` so the task prompt matches the real workflow.
3. Replace the starter cases in `cases.json`.
4. Confirm `candidates/V1/skill/` contains the baseline skill package you want to improve.
5. Optionally keep `cases.csv` in sync if spreadsheet editing is helpful.

## Core loop

```bash
# Run the active candidate
python3 run_eval.py --candidate V1

# Open the local grading app
python3 review_server.py --project-dir .

# Draft the next candidate after grading the fixed review batch
python3 optimize_skill.py draft-next --from V1

# Run the next candidate
python3 run_eval.py --candidate V2

# Stage a winning candidate after holdout clears
python3 promote_candidate.py stage --candidate V2
```

## What gets created

- `candidates/V1/skill/`: baseline imported skill
- later `candidates/V2/skill/`, `candidates/V3/skill/`, ...
- `outputs/raw/`: per-case logs and raw results per candidate
- `outputs/reports/`: candidate summaries and improvement prompts
- `review/grades.json`: local human grades
- `promotion/staged/`: staged winners awaiting approval
- `review-ui/`: local browser review app

## Simple workflow

1. define or import cases
2. run the current candidate
3. grade the fixed review batch in the browser
4. create the next candidate revision
5. rerun and compare
6. use the holdout gate to decide whether a version can be promoted
